// "BEATING": State indicating heart is beating (set to 1)
// "STOPPED": State indicating heart has stopped (set to 0)
// "PACEMAKER_DELAY": Maximum time to deliver pace after heart stops (in ticks) (set to 2)
// "heartState": Current state of the heart (initial value: BEATING)
// === System Behavior (Timed) ===
// Pacemaker: heart beats every 5 ticks. If heart stops, pacemaker detects within 2 ticks and delivers pacing pulse.
// Process Heart: Heart beats naturally every 5 time units.
// Process Pacemaker: Monitors heartbeat. If heart stops, delivers pace within 2 ticks.
// Timing requirements:
// - heart beats every 5 ticks
// - pacemaker responds within 2 ticks


// define the pacemaker system: overall system combining all the subsystems interleavingly ("|||"), consider defining the system around the most central variable (e.g., the number of owners) only if appropriate
// define **exactly** the following states and assertions as specified. Do **NOT** add, modify, or omit anything
// assert pacemaker system deadlockfree
// Define pacing_ok where heart always eventually beats. Assert pacing_ok holds.

The PAT code should be:
