// "GATE_UP": Gate is in the raised (open) position (set to 0)
// "GATE_DOWN": Gate is in the lowered (closed) position (set to 1)
// "GATE_LOWER_DURATION": Number of ticks the gate stays lowered after being triggered (set to 2)
// "trainState": Current state of the train in the crossing process (initial value: APPROACHING)
// "gateState": Current state of the gate (up or down) (initial value: GATE_UP)
// "gateTimer": Remaining ticks until gate is raised; 0 means gate is up or not in lowering phase (initial value: 0)
// === System Behavior (Timed) ===
// Railway: train approaches bridge, controller lowers gate. Train must not cross while gate is up. Controller lowers gate within 2 ticks after approach.
// Process Train: Train approaches bridge, waits for gate, crosses, then leaves.
// Process Controller: Detects approaching train, lowers gate for 2 ticks, then raises.
// Timing requirements:
// - gate lowered within 2 ticks after approach


// define the railway_control system: overall system combining all the subsystems interleavingly ("|||"), consider defining the system around the most central variable (e.g., the number of owners) only if appropriate
// define **exactly** the following states and assertions as specified. Do **NOT** add, modify, or omit anything
